    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="998"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d998">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 703.3212/5a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of today<note n="81" xml:id="d998fn81">Not printed.</note> has been
                    communicated to us by the Brazilian Ambassador, Glad to know that you are now in
                    charge of the records, archives, etc. Please assure the British Legation of our
                    appreciation of their courtesies and the valuable service rendered by them
                    during the time they acted for us.</p>
                <p>You are authorized to comply with the request of the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    that you deliver over the arms remaining in the Embassy to the police
                    authorities.</p>
                <p>It might be well for the present for you to send a brief telegram every night
                    before retiring, giving us the general situation there, so that we may be able
                    to answer questions that are asked us each morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
